-- Stephen Strasburg Wins 15th Game as Nationals Defeat Braves 4-1
-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 2012-08-22T04:01:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-22/stephen-strasburg-wins-15th-game-as-nationals-defeat-braves-4-1.html
Stephen Strasburg  struck out 10
batters while allowing one run on four hits in six innings to
pick up his 15th win of the season as the Washington Nationals
defeated the Atlanta Braves 4-1.  Strasburg (15-5) lowered his earned run average this season
to 2.85 as Washington improved to 77-46, best in Major League
Baseball. Atlanta (70-53) fell seven games behind the Nationals
in the National League East division with its fourth straight
loss.  Jesus Flores hit a three-run homer and Ian Desmond added a
solo home run for Washington at Nationals Park. Freddie Freeman
drove in Atlantaâ€™s only run with a sacrifice fly.  To contact the reporter on this story:
